  "prompt": "How much does it cost to make a music video?",
  "response": "The cost of making a music video can vary widely depending on several factors:\n\nBudget Ranges:\n1. Low-budget/DIY video: $500 - $5,000\n- Shot on basic equipment\n- Simple concept\n- Often done by indie artists\n\n2. Mid-range video: $5,000 - $50,000\n- Professional equipment\n- More complex production\n- Multiple locations\n- Basic special effects\n\n3. High-end/Major label video: $100,000 - $500,000+\n- Advanced cinematography\n- Complex storylines\n- Professional actors\n- Advanced special effects\n- Famous directors\n- Top-tier production quality\n\nFactors affecting cost:\n- Location costs\n- Equipment rental\n- Crew wages\n- Actors/dancers\n- Wardrobe\n- Makeup/styling\n- Post-production editing\n- Special effects\n- Number of shooting days\n- Director's reputation\n\nMany independent artists now create videos using smartphone cameras and basic editing software, significantly reducing costs. Some artists even crowdfund or collaborate with film students to create affordable videos.\n\nThe final price depends on the artist's vision, budget, and production complexity.",
